page.title: 09How Laceby got its name
page.content: From about the year 800AD the Vikings started to raid this part of the coast with the Humber being an ideal place for them to get further inland.Later they began to settle in this area anf the Vikings called the people of this area the Suthan Hymbro-(South Humbrians). It is from this origin that Laceby got its name. The "by" is Danish for-farm,homstead or settlement.The "Lace" is believed to come from many mispronounciations from the name "Lief"a common Norse surname.Thus Liefsby-the settlement of Leif-becomes Laceby. Some of the different spellings of our village have been Levesbi,Leuesby,Lesbi,Layseby,Leuseby, Leseby,Leisseby,Lesseby,Leyseby, Laifsebi,Lasby,Lacabie and Lusby.
